text: Whisky Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Washington. It is a tributary of the Touchet River. Whisky Creek most likely was named for two local men who sold whiskey to Indians. ==See also== *List of rivers of Washington ==References== Category:Rivers of Columbia County, Washington Category:Rivers of Walla Walla County, Washington Category:Rivers of Washington (state)
title: Whisky Creek (Touchet River tributary)
